cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on caching in a Named Data Networking (NDN) router and its impact on upstream bandwidth reduction. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible category as NDN is a security-focused network architecture. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a novel mathematical framework for evaluating caching performance in a non-zero download delay context. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper considers the impact of time locality in demand due to finite content lifetimes. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper evaluates the effectiveness of an LRU filter in improving caching performance.
